ratings.rComments: Very hilarious professor. Easy A class and reading doesn't matter too much.
Online homework is easy. labs and exams are very hard, you are aloud a cheat sheet on the exam but no matter how much info you put on it the exams are still to difficult for a 100 level intro course

This was supposed to be an easy A gen ed but it was not easy. There was so much homework and the tests were really, really hard even with the cheat sheet you can use. Bryan is super nice but I just wish the exams were a little easier and that the lectures were shorter!

Pretty easy class. It doesn't require alot of understanding, but you need to be able to memorize, then A's are very possible for exams, just allow 1hr study per lecture (exams cover 7-8 lectures). Homework quizzes allow 3 attempts, so those are guaranteed 100%s. Not a hard class... getting an A but I don't feel I learned THAT much, to be honest
He talks down on you when you have a question or need clarification.  He can be very rude to students. His class is easy and what you need to know is straight forward.

Very enthusiastic person, but teaching style is very confusing. The materials that are on the test is often not on the study guide, you basically have to remember every bit of the stuff he says in lecture.
His class was interesting, homework load was fair. discussions were easy. but when exams came, they were pretty hard. wish there were practice exams instead of TA reviewing the materials.
Weekly online homework answers can be found online. Lectures and activities were pretty interesting. You can tell he cares about the topic. Tests aren't the hardest and aren't the easiest.
This class was pretty tough due to the exams. You did get a cheat sheet, but sometimes it was not helpful at all. You really need to know the concept. The lectures were quite long also.

I mean he's a nice guy and the weekly assignments/work load are not bad at all, but the exams are literally impossible. Cheat sheet doesn't help, and some of the questions I've never seen before in the lectures. He's not too bad but the exams are honestly HORRIBLE.

Very easy midterms and exam if you had done your homework and went to lectures (I studied less than 3 hours, 3 hours, 5 hours)  Lectures are enjoyable, and the professor gives off a great vibe. Easy classes, easy to follow.

Overall, it's an easy class. All the homework can be found online, and the labs are not too bad. He gives several extra credit opportunities, but his exams are extremely difficult. He lets you use a cheat sheet, but it doesn't help much. Even if you don't do that well on the exams, as long as you do everything else you should be fine.
Even though he lets students use cheatsheet on the exam, you'll find it mostly useless because exams are extremely hard. (But I think he curves grades as well)
Incredibly funny and engaging lectures, not a dull moment.
Dunne is freaking awesome! Take his classes!

He is a overall great teacher. He is super enthusiastic and loves teaching astronomy. There is a lot of work in his classes, but he is fair with due dates. The tests are pretty hard, so you have to go to class and read the book.

2 exams and cumulative final. 3 easy science projects. 2 reports - 3rd one for extra credit. Mandatory iclicker - every answer right is extra credit. Often curves exams about 5%. Really enthusiastic about teaching. Interesting lectures most of the time. Do the extra credit and you'll get an A

Professor Dunne has been, by far, my favorite professor on campus. He is extremely smart, always prepared, uses technology in lectures very effectively, is always helpful and willing to help, in such a good mood it's almost alarming, and has the funniest sense of humor! Book was cheap used & not required. Lectures were optional, but had i>clickers.
Great professor. Very enthusiastic about astronomy and is entertaining in lecture. Lets you use a double-sided note sheet during the midterms and final. A great class to take for the science gen-ed.

Bryan Dunne is an incredibly good professor. As I am thinking about it, I actually have never had a professor who was so enthusiastic and effective. Professor Dunne really cares about making the students enjoy and learn as much as possible in his class. I would recommend this class to anyone and everyone.

He is the absolute best! So enthusiastic about his job which makes learning from him that much better. Not a hard class at all either. DON'T take Celeste for your discussion section. She isn't helpful at all.
Very organized. Easy A. Do the extra credit!

Easily one of my favorite professors on campus. He's very enthusiastic about what he teaches, and he's always in an outstanding mood and is eager to answer any questions you may have. Go to lectures! Not only are iclickers part of your grade, but the lectures are just plain fun to go to. Take this class!

Easy and enjoyable :)...I miss this class.  It's one of the few classes where I learned a lot from.  Just go over the homework/quiz answers for the test and you're good to go.  Don't bother watching the lectures on youtube...they are far too long.

Prof. Dunne is easily one of my favorite professors at this university. I look forward to going to his class three days a week (he's my discussion teacher, too.) He makes class so much fun and he makes these cheesy and relevant jokes. He keeps you interested and awake in class. He's actually the best.

I'm only taking the class because I wanted to add a course mid semester and it was a second half online course. Easy is an understatement. As long as you go over the material it is not hard to grasp. The professor for his online video lecture though speaks way too slow, monotone, and pauses too long making them near impossible to go through.

Sadly, I got a B+ when it was an easy A course because I didn't do half of the online quizzes.  I only attended half the classes and it was still extremely easy.  The quizzes are just like the tests, so use them to your advantage!  He's an interesting lecturer.
AKA Peter Griffin, BEST TEACHER! FUNNY GUY, MAKES CLASS ENJOYABLE AND SOMETHING WORTH GOING TO. Could not have asked for a better teacher.
Amazing teacher. You dont really NEED to go to class, but I always do because I love it. The dorky humor, the mind blowing facts, the enthusiasm, this guy is awesome.

Simply the best professor at the U of I.  His lectures are not only effective, but actually very fun.  The class itself was very interesting, but Dr. D made it enjoyable.  I am actually considering sitting in on this class again this semester.  If you can, take ASTRO 150 with Bryan Dunne.
Very nice guy! love his class!

This teacher is just amazing; he is truly passionate about Astronomy. Also, his class is extremely easy which gives it another plus. For his tests you can bring in a sheet of notes to use and final is just another test. I finished with A+, and had a great time listening to him in lectures.
He is hilarious and very helpful! He explains everything very well and in a way that is interesting. I'd definitely take another class of his!
This is a great class. He's a very fun teacher and makes the class awesome. Easy to get a good grade!
Fantastic class

Dr. Dunne is an extremely good professor. He is very passionate about the subject matter and class is enjoyable. He gives generous extra credit oppotunities and their are daily iclicker points to help boost your grade. As long as you put in a little effort this class is a very easy A. Highly recommended!

Overall was a very easy class if you go to class and pay attention. There are iclicker points. There is one midterm and a final for tests. Homework load isnt bad and is easy for the most part. Take this class for a gen ed!

BEST CLASS I TOOK THIS YEAR! Weekly assessments but you get two tries, you get a double-sided cheat sheet for the midterm and final, and you have opportunity to replace midterm exam grade on the final. Dunne truly is "delightfully geeky" and I loved going to class everyday. What a gen-ed should always feel like! Take this class for phys science!

One of the fairest classes I've had. Dunne gives you plenty of opportunities to ace the class. There's weekly online homework, but you get two opportunities to do it. Exams can be a little tough but doable if you study. Show up to lectures to get easy Iclicker points. A few online labs but they're pretty interesting. Great class, great professor!
Very easy b/c you get a page of notes for your tests. He posts notes online and there is so many opportunities to get an A. Just do the work

Very eccentric and passionate, this prof is delightfully geeky.  Everything is online, you only get a grade for your best 2 out of 3 observing sessions, best 25 scores in lecture, and likewise for other assignments.  The only reason to go to class is the points u get from the iClicker quizes.  Study for the exams & you'll do fine.  EXCELLENT GEN ED

Great professor. Very, very enthusiastic about the subject matter and you can hear it in his voice. Class isn't hard- exam q's are from past quizzes and i-clicker q's not to mention that Dunne is EXTREMELY helpful. He's also pretty funny in a nerdy way--makes the class that much more interesting. If you're gonna take Astro 100, take it with Dunne!
I dont know what everyone is talking about...the professor is kind of okay but his class sucks! I hate astronomy and his class puts me to sleep. Its not easy. Dont take it.

Professor Dunne is one of my favorite professors at the university. He is kind and will do his utmost to help students. He is funny and keeps the class entertaining. He is extremely enthusiastic about Astronomy. I have found this class to be really interesting. It's also pretty easy to get an A in the class!
Dunne is awesome.  This is one of those classes everybody dreams of.  You have to take this class.

Class is interesting. Tests are fair (straight from notes/online hw/old exams). Dunne tries really hard to keep it funny and interesting. Sometimes it's overboard, but overall he's a great professor and it's sincerely interested that everybody understands.
What a lovely, squirrely fellow.
Awesome class, great professor, highly recommended!
This class is super easy as long as you go to most of the classes.  He puts all the notes online, so even if you don't go, its no big deal!  I recommend it if you need a gen ed!

Fun, interesting class.  Learn a lot of not too difficult material.  Good lecture slides with good attempts at humor.  Don't need a prior understanding of advanced physics or anything.  Exams are relatively easy.  Online quizzes weekly.  Discussion is a blast.
Absolutely incredible professor.  Highly recommended!!!
Possibly the best class I have ever taken.  I learned a great deal, was hardly ever bored, and content was explained excellently.  Dunne is a fantastic professor.
